      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:29:8",
      "text": [
        " سَأَلْتُهُ عَنِ الرَّجُلِ يَفْتَرِي عَلَى امْرَأَتِهِ قَالَ يُجْلَدُ ثُمَّ يُخَلَّى بَيْنَهُمَا وَ لَا يُلَاعِنُهَا حَتَّى يَقُولَ أَشْهَدُ أَنَّنِي رَأَيْتُكِ تَفْعَلِينَ كَذَا وَ كَذَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Hammad, from Hareyz, from Muhammad Bin Muslim who said, ",
          "‘I asked him<sup>asws</sup> about the man who fabricated upon his wife. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘He would be whipped, then there would be separation between the two, and he would not curse her until he is saying, ‘I testify that I saw you, such and such being done with you’."
        ]
      }
